<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6b3b43f4-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s521"><num value="521">§ 521.</num><heading> Regulations and orders</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary is authorized to prescribe such rules and regulations, and to make and issue such orders, as may be necessary or appropriate for carrying out the provisions of this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6b3b43f5-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/act/1940-06-21/ch409/s11">June 21, 1940, ch. 409, § 11</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/54/501">54 Stat. 501</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
